text.tspan: Suicide rate vs. death rate from violence (per 100,000), 2016
Death rate from suicide versus death rate from violence or murder, measured per 100,000 individuals. Deaths from
violence include the categories of interpersonal violence (homicide), conflict and terrorism, and police conflict and
executions. A line of parity (where suicide rate equals violent deaths rate) is also shown.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
